controlling a greyhound cross tried haltis did not work then went on to a harness worked for a few months but she now knows how to back up and take her legs out very quickly and escape so far managed to grab her in time but as she is a very nervous dog if a bus goes by and she escapes before i can catch her i am afraid what will happen it is a good quality harness goes around her chest and under her shoulders i do not know how she manages it it is as tight as it will go she is very slim and long necked with slim shoulders i am at my wits end going out for a walk is no joy with a jumpy dog but it is worse now knowing that she could get under the wheels of a bus she is crossed with a belgium shepherd i stay as calm as possible i am cosidering the martingale collar and keep the harness on her too along with leads she is a lot better than she was when i got her months ago then she jumped if anything moved in the wind she was in a kennel for first year of her life and she is only learning about things trouble is i take dogs out a springer as well springer is great but pulls when the greyhound freaks i am going to have popeye arms soon thankyou to all i found a site eventually called kitschcollars co uk really brill martingale collars for greyhounds she is sending one out asap hopefully this will do the trick you really need a greyhound leash martingale collar and leash all in one piece any greyhound is going to fight a halti like crazy and most likely a harness as well what's she crossed with greyhounds do not need any type of choke collar if she's nervous she needs socializing start in quiet areas at quieter times of day and gradually work your up to more traffic and noise also how do you react when she panics if you get tense and nervous that travels right down the leash to the dog and she thinks she's right to be afraid she thinks she has a reason to be afraid if you tighten up the leash or tell her it's ok you need to be able to walk that fine line between being ther